_entry\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/collocations/indictment\" title=\" definition in Collocations\n \">full entry</a></span></span></span></div>          \n</li><li class=\"sense\" hclass=\"sense\" sensenum=\"2\" htag=\"li\" id=\"indictment_sng_2\" cefr=\"c2\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"grammar\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"grammar\">[countable]</span></span> <span class=\"labels\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"labels\">(especially North American English)</span> <span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">an official statement accusing somebody of a crime</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">She was convicted on an indictment for conspiracy.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The federal district court dismissed the indictment.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The government announced a federal indictment against him.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">They issued an indictment against them.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">Two men were named in the indictment.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">War crimes indictments were handed down by a UN-backed court.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">an indictment charging theft</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">There is sufficient evidence against him to support an indictment for murder.</span></li></ul><span class=\"topic-g\"><span class=\"prefix\">Topics </span><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/law-and-justice?level=c2\" title=\"Topic law-and-justice\"><span class=\"topic\" href=\"l2:politics_and_society:law_and_justice?cefr=c2\"><span class=\"topic_name\">Law and justice</span><span class=\"topic_cefr\">c2</span></span></a></span><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" h